Governor Muhammad Badaru Abubakar of Jigawa State has inaugurated the state All Progressives Congress APC, executives. The governor inaugurated the party executives on Monday at the party’s headquarters in Dutse, the state capital of the state. He warned the executives of the party to commit themselves and work harder for the victory of the party in the 2023 general election. “I am warning all the party executives from wards, local governments and state to work for the unity and progress of the party” “You equally have to be just and carry every member along for the victory of the party” The state Chairman of the party Aminu Sani Gumel, however, commended Governor Muhammad Badaru for his commitments towards the party congresses which lead to the emergence of the executives. The party’s executive inauguration is coming days after the Acting interim National Chairman of the Party and Governor of Niger State Abubakar Sani Bello swore in Aminu Sani Gumel and other state chairmen of the party in Abuja.